Source: jdbc-fdw
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), libpq-dev, default-jdk-headless
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/pgspider/jdbc_fdw

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-jdbc-fdw
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-jdbc-fdw
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, default-jre-headless, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: JDBC foreign data wrapper for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
 jdbc_fdw connects PostgreSQL to remote JDBC data sources through an embedded
 JVM. A suitable JDBC driver JAR and remote database are required for queries.
